comments.body: Yes, agree that Jutta Arctic does appear a better match, and they have been recorded in the region.
how about Jutta arctic?  i am no expert, just reading the butterflies of Canada book.

results.description: Observed near Margaret Lake, in sub-alpine habitat.  Possibly Chryxus Arctic, but not sure.

identifications.body: Pale area surrounding eyespot is present on forewing underside, and appears to be on upperside also.  Pattern on hindwing underside is good match for Oeneis jutta; overall colouration and eyespots with white pupils.
